Title: Layout.AdditionalSettings["barsPerRow"]
JsName: layout.mode.additionalSettings.barsPerRow
DataAttribute: data-layout-bars-per-row
Category: Layout
Description: Limit the displayed bars per row.
Since: 0.9.4
ShowInSideBar: false
---

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>
    This setting sets the number of bars that should be put into one row. 
    <a href="@Context.GetLink("/features/layouts")#page-layout-5-bars">Demo</a>
</p>

<h2>Types</h2>

<table class="table table-striped table-condensed type-table">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Values</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>    
    <tbody>    
        <tr>
            <td><code>int <span class="code-badge">all</span></td>
            <td>
                <code>-1/code> - Automatic<br />
                <code>5</code>
            </td>
        </tr>   
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Default Value</h2>

<code>-5<code>

<h2>Example - C#</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-csharp line-numbers">
var settings = Settings.Defaults;
settings.Layout.AdditionalSettings["barsPerRow"] = 5;
</code>
</pre>


<h2>Example - JavaScript</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-javascript line-numbers">
var settings = {
    layout: {
        additionalSettings: {
            barsPerRow: 5
        }
    }    
};
var api = new alphaTab.platform.javaScript.AlphaTabApi(document.querySelector('#alphaTab'), settings);
var japi = $('#alphaTab').alphaTab(settings);
</code>
</pre>

<h2>Example - HTML</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-html line-numbers">
&lt;div id="alphaTab" data-layout-bars-per-row="5"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</code>
</pre>
